 spectral\nimaging method to general astrophysics will facilitate further research. The\nbeam combiner and spectral imaging method are applied to a formation-flying\nstellar interferometer with multiple small satellites in a Sun-synchronous\norbit for observation of the solar system objects in visible and near-infrared.\nWe present an overview of SEIRIOS and the optimized optical design for a\nlimited-volume spacecraft.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 Jan 2022 23:21:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-20"}
