nder collision region for different values of $\\sigma$ are\npresented both for inviscid flow and for viscous flow with moderately large\nvalues of the controlling Reynolds number $\\Gamma/\\nu$. The velocity\ndescription provided is useful in mathematical formulations of localized\nfire-whirl flows, providing consistent boundary conditions accounting for the\nambient swirl level.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 19 Jan 2022 10:31:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-20"}
